Israeli Stocks: Cellcom Israel, RadVision, Perrigo

-- B y   S h o s h a n n a   S o l o m o n
-- 
2011-12-04T15:54:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-04/israeli-stocks-cellcom-israel-radvision-are-active.html
Israel’s  TA-25 Index (TA-25)  declined less
than 0.1 percent to 1,084.33 at the 4:30 p.m. close in  Tel Aviv ,
the lowest since Nov. 30. Investors traded about 538 million
shekels ($144 million) of shares and convertible securities,
according to bourse data.  The following stocks rose or fell today. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Cellcom Israel Ltd. (CEL)   dropped to the lowest since
listing in July 2007, declining 3.4 percent to 61.90 shekels.
The nation’s biggest mobile-phone operator said it will dismiss
140 workers as part of a merger with NetVision Ltd.  Perrigo Co. (PRGO)   rose to the highest level since the
shares listed in Tel Aviv in March 2005, gaining 2.3 percent to
373.50 shekels. The stock gained before “its entry to the
Nasdaq 100 index next Tuesday,” Saar Golan, a trader at Clal
Finance Batucha Brokerage Ltd. said in an e-mailed note today.  RadVision Ltd. (RVSN)   jumped the most since at least
October 2002 when Bloomberg started tracking the data, gaining
30 percent to 23.62 shekels, or the equivalent of $6.30. The
shares of the maker of video-conferencing systems narrowed the
gap with the U.S.-traded shares. RadVision gained 31 percent to
$6.29 in the last two days of trading in  New York  last week.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shoshanna Solomon in Tel Aviv at 
